TWENTY-FOURTH NORTHERN MARIANAS COMMONWEALTH
LEGISLATURE
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
SESSION, 2025 H. L. B. 24- S
A LOCAL APPROPRIATION BILL FOR AN ACT
FOR THE THIRD SENATORIAL DISTRICT
To appropriate the remaining fund balance of $85,500.00 under Saipan
Local Law 23-04 for the repair, maintenance and improvements of
recreational facilities in Precinct IV; and for other purposes.
BE IT ENACTED BY THE THIRD SENATORIAL DISTRICT
DELEGATION PURSUANT TO CHAPTER 4, DIVISION 1, TITLE 1 OF
THE COMMONWEALTH CODE:
1 SECTION 1. PURPOSE.
2 The purpose of this Act is to appropriate the remaining fund balance of
3 $85,500.00 under Saipan Local Law 23-04, Section 2(t)(1)(a) for the repair,
4 maintenance, and improvements of recreational facilities in Precinct IV and for
5 other purposes.
6 SECTION 2. RE-APPROPRIATION.
7 Notwithstanding any provision(s) of law, statutes, rules or regulations to the
8 contrary and pursuant to funds allocated to the Third Senatorial District the Saipan
9 and Northern Islands Legislative Delegation (SNILD) hereby appropriates the

HOUSE LOCAL BILL 24- S
1 remaining fund balance of $85,500.00 under Saipan Local Law 23-04, Section
2 2(t)(1)(a); as follows:
3 (A) Eighty-Five Thousand Five Hundred dollars ($85,500.00) to the Natibu
4 Sports Association in collaboration with Division of Parks and
5 Recreation for the repair, maintenance, and improvements of the Capitol
6 Hill Softball Field in Precinct IV.
7 SECTION 3. EXPENDITURE AUTHORITY
8 The expenditure authority for the funds under Section 2(A) shall be the
9 President of NSA in direct collaboration with the Director of Parks and Recreation.
10 SECTION 4. REPROGRAMMING.
11 Notwithstanding any laws, provisions, or regulations to the contrary, funds
12 appropriated under this act shall not be reprogrammed for any other purpose.
13 SECTION 5. FISCAL YEAR.
14 The funds allocated under this Act shall be without fiscal year limitation(s).
15 SECTION 6. REPORTING OF EXPENDITURES.
16 Expenditures of the funds allocated under Section 2 of this Act shall be
17 responsible to report all expenses to the Chairperson of the Saipan and Northern
18 Islands Legislative Delegation a detail report showing the expenditure of the funds.
19 Provided further that failure to provide all expenses, entities that were afforded
20 funds under this Act shall not be able to avail to any future funds appropriated by
21 the Saipan and Northern Islands Legislative Delegation.
2

HOUSE LOCAL BILL 24- S
1 SECTION 7. FUND DISTRIBUTION.
2 Funds appropriated under Section 2 of this Act shall be distributed
3 accordingly to the intended purpose and or entity upon this Act becoming law.
4 SECTION 8. SEVERABILITY.
5 If any provision of this Act or the application of any such provision to any
6 person or circumstance should be held invalid by a court of competent jurisdiction,
7 the remainder of this Act or the application of its provisions to persons or
8 circumstances other than those to which it is held invalid shall not be affected
9 thereby.
10 SECTION 9. SAVINGS CLAUSE.
11 This Act and any repealer contained herein shall not be construed as
12 affecting any existing right acquired under contract or acquired under statutes
13 repealed or under any rule, regulation or order adopted under the statutes. Repealers
14 contained in this Act shall not affect any proceeding instituted under or pursuant to
15 prior law. The enactment of the Act shall not have the effect of terminating, or in
16 any way modifying, any liability, civil or criminal, which shall already be in
17 existence on the date this Act becomes effective.
18 SECTION 10. EFFECTIVE DATE.
19 This Act shall take effect upon its approval by the Governor or it becoming
20 law without such approval.
